It was the Weekend of Love when she saw him again.  All kinds of people -- human, barbarian, iksar, half-elf and all kinds of elves -- were gathered to help save the Nektulos guards and the young they defended from persecution.  It was fitting that the majority of prizes for their rally were Validus Custodus arms from the service of Katta Castellum.<br>
<br>
He appeared on the edge of the tunnel overlooking the east common plains.  Though he still held his back stiffly, the joy of seeing him again overwhelmed the pain she felt him still suffering.  But before they could speak much, there was a griffin to be defeated so the games may safely begin.<br>
<br>
A long while later, after the games were over and the rally had subsided into festivities, she sent her mind outward to find him again.  She asked if maybe he’d have a minute for her to give him a shield to go with the axe he’d won.  She wasn’t sure if he’d like it, but she wanted him to have it.  He finally agreed to meet in Lavastorm, and she was there soon after.  <br>
<br>
He studied the shield when she presented it, amazed at its durable construction despite the lightweight design.  She said it was a Combine shield, and when asked she said that she supported what the Combine Empire once tried to be, rather than the silly sham folks were trying to remake it into.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Shiden says, 'I must say I was surprised to see such a number of races gathered in friendship.  Perhaps you can achieve what was failed by the Empire.'</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
She smiled with hope at his words while he slipped the shield onto his arm.  He then reached behind to unclasp he axe from his back and wield it.  Kimaya clapped, cooing over how fierce he looked!  Then she sighed, and when asked again, said it was because she SO wanted to kiss him but she knew he wouldn’t let her.  <br>
<br>
He suddenly sped off without a word, leaving tracks for her to follow into a hidden corner of the mountains.  <br>
