<br>
Their swords drawn, their tongues flicking forth every impure language on Norrath, their armor shiny and polished, all left no doubt in his mind that this small group of lightbringers were going to assault Neriak.  He swore that he saw a few rogue Teir'dal as well, but he wasn't surprised; many a youth of Neriak falls under the sway of goodness.<br>
<br>
Shiden sent word back to the lodge and prepared to meet them.  They greatly outnumbered him and were easily more powerful, but that does not matter in the life of a knight; he went out alone to meet them, his sword drawn and his helmet in his hand.<br>
<br>
It was a shock to find they were there to help defend Nektulos and stop those who would slaughter the fine guardsmen who patrol those bleak woods.  Throughout the rally, Shiden's mood lifted.  He let down his guard, put away his weapon.  He watched in humor as they all tried to run to the border of Nektulos from the tunnel which connects the commonlands to the desert of Ro.  That particular event he could have won, since he had ran it so often, but enjoyed watching the others stumble drunkenly too much to take first.  His prize, although second, had been a most impressive looking axe, and it had come at such an opportune time, saving him the trouble of looking for a worthy weapon to wield along with a shield.<br>
<br>
His guard went back up though when the elf who organized the event wished to meet him in Lavastorm.<br>
<br>
&quot;And what is the catch, Wood Elf?  Are you attempting to bribe me to forget the wrongs your kind has suffered upon my people?&quot;<br>
<br>
The druid stammered over her words, babbling some nonsense about pixies.  Shiden weighed her words carefully - if it were a trap he would not leave Lavastorm.  It was a sacrifice Shiden decided he would take if he could strike down one of his city's enemies.<br>
<br>
In the bright red of Lavastorm, Shiden called out for the druid to meet him.<br>
<br>
&quot;Well here you go, cutie!&quot;<br>
<br>
Shiden spun, not familiar with the tricks of Wood Elves and Druids.  How she had crept up on him he did not know, but he imagined it was with the use of odd magic.  Nevertheless, she stood before him, a huge shield held out in her hands.  Shiden eyed her warily, and after she assured him that the shield was not cursed, he took it.<br>
<br>
The design was unfamiliar, but this shield was better than anything he could buy in Neriak.  Despite its huge size and strong build, it was half as light as the sword he was used to swinging.<br>
<br>
&quot;Ooh, it's a Combine shield!&quot; explained the wood elf.  Shiden looked at her bright smile and happy eyes and sighed inwardly.  So that is what she wants me here for, he mused.  To try and pull me from my duty at Neriak like so many other young Teir'dal.<br>
<br>
While he asked her about the shield and tried to find out if she did indeed mean to make him 'good,' he strapped on the shield and grabbed the axe from his back.  The balance was a nice one, which pleased him.  He would have to venture to the Isle of the Sisters to bathe the two properly.<br>
<br>
Shiden looked up to find the druid pouting melodramatically.  Cocking an eye, he asked her what was the matter.<br>
<br>
&quot;Oh goodness, I don't even know HOW to lie!&quot; she said with a laugh.  The sound made Shiden's ears hurt. &quot;Um, well...well, cause I kinda wanna kiss you, but I don't think you'll let me!&quot;<br>
<br>
Shiden blinked.  How can she be so forward!  To think I would bed a pale and forget the pride of my people!<br>
<br>
He looked at her for a second more and decided that there wasn't a chance of him killing her.  The only other option was to run.<br>
<br>
Unfortunately for Shiden, the bleak stone of Lavastorm makes it easy to lose your way.  When he started running, it was in the wrong direction. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ukimayasilverbark.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kimaya Silverbark</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://prod.bsis.bellsouth.net/coDataImages/bellsouthpwp/Groups/15/15568/folders/6507/Thumbnails/67125button-wolf-pawprint" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Tao Te Bark</span><br>  Posts: 254<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(5/29/02 3:20:39 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=289.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://home.bellsouth.net/coDataImages/bellsouthpwp/Groups/15/15568/pages/34736/Kimaya-60.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> The Joy</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Part II</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
She caught up with him easily, giggling at him as he leaned up against a rock and said something about her scent.  She told him it was roses and leaned in, sweeping her hair away so her bare neck was close to his face.  As she did so, he backed away nervously and tried to recompose himself.<br>
<br>
She laughed excitedly as he changed the subject to training and food, until he finally he turned away, apparently annoyed.  She tried tickling the back of his neck, and he only sputtered in frustration.  She blushed, certain she said something wrong.  He insisted she hadn’t, simply that she confused him.  She blushed even harder, since she did THAT a lot too.  He just looked at her a moment, then sighed again.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Shiden says, 'I...I don't know how to do what I must.'<br>
Kimaya says, 'And what must you do?', looking at him curiously.<br>
Shiden looks Kimaya in the eyes.<br>
Shiden says, 'Hate you.'</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
She laughed, and when he said it was Innoruuk who said he had to, she just laughed even harder and called the god a Hatey Liar who would smear him across the rocks and say he hated the stain he made.  <br>
<br>
She tried to explain to him how people made themselves, using their own power from within, regardless of what any god ever says.  She said he had dreams of wives and children in the Karanas, and it wouldn’t be easy, but finding them would be as simple as walking away.  He wouldn’t be the first, or even the second to do so.  <br>
<br>
He shook his head and swore she just didn’t understand, she couldn’t...  Though he felt he belonged howhere, Nektulos and Lavastorm were his home.  He told her he had tried to walk a different path, and then he decided to show her the price he paid for it.<br>
<br>
He tore off his armor and bore his midsection to her, exposing a multitude of scars that circled around his abdomen and back.  She bit her lip, inadvertently reaching out her hand as it started to almost glow... then caught herself before she touched him.  She remembered what had happened with Kallee, and didn’t want to get yelled at again.<br>
<br>
Holding her hand back, she shyly looked down.  She then glanced back up at him to admit that she could heal his scars, if he would let her touch them.  He forbade her from doing so, calling them a hideous badge of honor.  They were signs that he had gone through pain that the whelps of Neriak could not imagine and he lived, crawling himself up from the dirt.<br>
<br>
She nodded, puzzled again at people’s ideas about something nebulous like “honor”. But as he talked, she saw the strength he had gained from overcoming those horrors, and imagined what he may have been like someday if he were able to overcome all the torments that faced him.  If he was strong enough to pursue his dreams...<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Shiden says, 'You are only the second person to see my scars.'<br>
Kimaya looks away, then replies, 'I'd like to be the first to see you someday grow strong enough that you don’t need to cling to them, reminding yourself you’re strong.'</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/umadrain.showPublicProfile?language=EN>madrain</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Kerran Lord</span><br>  Posts: 366<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(5/29/02 4:35:46 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=289.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> The Hate</span><hr size=1> Part II<br>
<br>
&quot;Caught ya!&quot;<br>
<br>
Shiden fell against a large monolithic stone, completely winded.  Running had been hard on him since he had joined the Lodge of the Dead again, and running with armor on was even harder.  How she had managed to follow him, to constantly find him despite his best attempts at hiding, was beyond him.  He was sure this would end badly.  Let the witch kill me, he thought to himself.  Rather dead than a lightlover.<br>
<br>
Suddenly an idea formed in his head.  He turned to face her, leaning still against the rock.  His eyes squinted as he spoke.<br>
<br>
&quot;I can smell you, you know.  I smell the same glistening scent that clings to the purity belts I take from the Sisters of Erollisi Marr.&quot;<br>
<br>
The druid giggled.  &quot;Oh boy, they SAY they don't do that, but...&quot; She leaned in to whisper conspiratorially, &quot;...some of them know how ta pick locks.&quot;<br>
<br>
Shiden sighed and tried again.  &quot;I...I'm sorry I'm not a better cook.  I'd have brought you Wood Elf steaks.&quot;  He peered at her, gauging her reaction.<br>
<br>
&quot;Ooh, but I can cook!&quot; she replied helpfully.<br>
<br>
Shiden groaned.  Her happiness disgusted him.  Noone can be this happy and amiable.  Her gift for mirth apalled and scared him.  Very well.  If she can't be angered to leave, perhaps I can scare her away.<br>
<br>
Shiden explained that he must hate her because Innoruuk demands it.<br>
<br>
Still not understanding, he ripped his breastplate loose and exposed her bare chest to him.  Surely the scars would disgust her.  The ugly, long, jagged lines of bruised purple snaked their way around his belly and back.  They'd served to frighten away even experienced whores.  Go away, here be dragons.<br>
<br>
&quot;I hate your kind, Elf.  I hate them for making us what we are.&quot;<br>
<br>
They argued then, over Innoruuk and Tunare, over the humans and high elves and dark elves, over Freeport and Neriak.  They argued over honor.  Furious, Shiden yelled at her, tried to make her understand, but still she talked back calmly, as if happy to try and bring turmoil into his life.<br>
<br>
Exhausted and out of breath, Shiden sank against the rock and slid to the ground beneath him.  If anger and fire and brimstone would not work, perhaps the truth could be found in calm.<br>
<br>
So yet again he changed his tactics.  He told her how he despised Neriak's politics and how he knew that his dream of having a family would never be realized within that city and while his kind was still persecuted by the lightbringers.  He spoke of Lavastorm, and how fond he was of it.<br>
<br>
When she mentioned that Lavastorm brims with life, fostering even weeds that will grow nowhere else, he argued that to her people all Teir'dal were just weeds - easy to overlook when you don't see them, but once you want a pretty garden the only route is to kill it.<br>
<br>
&quot;Not my kind. No one is a weed to MY kind,&quot; she replied with a level of seriousness she had not shown before.<br>
<br>
Shiden looked at her and did his best to conceal his fury.  &quot;Then your kind must be very rare.&quot;<br>
<br>
He noticed how hard she was gripping her hammer and he fancied she would suddenly hit him with it, kill him like the weed that he was.  She'd go back to her friends and tell them to admire her new pretty garden now that one more weed is gone from it.  He would almost welcome the release from his responsibility as a knight.<br>
<br>
His responsibility.<br>
<br>
No!  Damn her, she will succumb to Hate! <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ukimayasilverbark.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kimaya Silverbark</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://prod.bsis.bellsouth.net/coDataImages/bellsouthpwp/Groups/15/15568/folders/6507/Thumbnails/67125button-wolf-pawprint" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Tao Te Bark</span><br>  Posts: 255<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(5/29/02 4:58:06 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=289.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://home.bellsouth.net/coDataImages/bellsouthpwp/Groups/15/15568/pages/34736/Kimaya-60.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> The... ?</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  Part III</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
Rather than answer, he looked down at the large hammer she was absently toying with.  He mused that perhaps he was already strong enough that she considered him a threat and was waiting to smash his face in. She giggled, insisting she was more likely waiting to SMOOCH his face in, then she playfully kissed his nose.<br>
<br>
He caught her before she could sit back and kissed her softly, catching a taste of Nepeta Cataria mint.  Surprised, she inhaled with a soft Mmmm that was muffled by his lips pressed against hers.  He then pulled back and looked at her, as if unsure what to say.  She looked down, biting her lip shyly with a hint of blush on her cheeks.  Perhaps it was her reactions he found irresistable, for it was his faint smile at her blushing that drew her in.<br>
<br>
He reached out, hesitant, then slowly let his fingers glide through her soft, silvery hair.  Though before he had said that only swinging a sword brought him pleasure, he said her hair was soft and pleasurable to the touch.  She beamed a smile, then started launching into a flurry of words about of how pleased she was since she had actually brushed her hair earlier and was SO afraid a pixie would put knots in it…<br>
<br>
He then caught the back of her head and kissed her suddenly before she could talk any more. She giggled softly then kissed him back, playfully nipping at his lip.  Closing his eyes, he ran his lips down her jaw and neck, nibbling just below her ear.  She shivered, giggling softly.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  Kimaya says, 'Tickles...'<br>
Shiden repeats, &quot;Tickles,&quot; softly into her ear, using the sultry voice he learned at The Maiden's Fancy.</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
From there, she fell into an almost hypnotic haze.  She giggled, they joked, he laughed.  Throughout it all she could feel she had brought him joy, which made her even happier to be near him.  He leaned her back against a rock, tracing Elder Teir'dal characters with his fingertips on the topmost inner part of her leg.  <br>
<br>
Giggling even harder at the tickling, she Kimaya moved her head, trying to see what he's drawing.  He admitted it was Elder Teir’Dal, though he only knew a little bit of it.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  Shiden says, 'Here.  Hold still, I'll trace my name on you,'  He starts with Shiden on her right thigh and goes through each character carefully until he ends Kaidan on her other leg.<br>
Kimaya beams with a bright smile, saying, 'And now you'll be close to me there forever!'<br>
Smiling back at her, Shiden says, 'I could be even closer...'</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
Though the details of the next few hours were lost to her in a haze of joy and pleasure, the laughter and the closeness they shared were unforgettable.  He had become an inescapable part of her, in a hidden part of her soul.<br>
<br>
After a while it began to rain, and it was time for them to each move on.  He re-equipped her gifts, then put his helmet back on to snarl at her, making her laugh and clap at the funny echo.  He joked that sometimes he forgot to remove his helmet before shouting, and his ears would ring for hours.  And though she couldn’t see it through the helm, she could feel that somewhere inside, he was smiling.<br>
<br>
When they parted, there was no awkwardness as to whether they would see each other again.  She knew they would, and she would see him happy.  She wouldn't wait again for a passing glimpse either, hiding shyly and camouflaged behind a rock.<br>
<br>
Sometimes it was better not to be shy.<br>
