<br>
She <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> will</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> succumb to Hate.<br>
<br>
Shiden was lost.  This was a puzzle too great for him.  The Nobles of Neriak would know just what to do, but during his lifetime he had been taught the ways of war, not of words and political maneuvering.  He now wished he could have guidance from some of the stronger knights he had met, knights like Kallee or Shintou or Velve.  Those knights were gone, lost to him then as he sat in Lavastorm, trapped and afraid for his soul.<br>
<br>
The hammer he had thought would leap towards his head at any moment was apparently just out to comfort her.  She smiled and joked with him about it.  Thankfully she hadn't seen the thin sweat break out on his forehead.<br>
<br>
While she put it away his mind flickered over what she had just said.  <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> More a chance to SMOOCH your head in!</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->  She'd said it when he asked if she was waiting for a chance to smash his head in.  Smooch his head in.<br>
<br>
She leaned in and kissed his nose, which he thought must have been some sort of weird Fier'dal custom.  An idea sparked.<br>
<br>
Quickly he grabbed her, forced her lips to his.  If she will not hate me for my race, she will hate me for this.  Innoruuk, guide me.  I'm afraid.<br>
<br>
&quot;Mm,&quot; she breathed softly.  Perhaps the masters of the Lodge knew he could gain some use from those skills he learned as a lad at The Maiden's Fancy.  He'd never understood why he could go there and nowhere else, even in the Third Gate.<br>
<br>
&quot;Mm as in Mm-inty?&quot; Shiden asked, trying not to vomit.  The wood elf had been chewing something horrible.  It burned his mouth and lips.<br>
<br>
Soon enough she was under his control.  She hung on each of his words, listening in rapture, laughing at his jokes.  He grabbed and poked and caressed what he pleased without restraint.  He toyed with her the same way he toyed with the whores of the Fancy.  He flirted, made her melt.  Made her feel like he was hers, when in reality it was the other way around.<br>
<br>
&quot;Here, hold still,&quot; he said to her as he spread her legs wide.  He slid his hands up her leather armor slowly, letting the sensations tantalize her while he prayed to his God.<br>
<br>
Put power in these words.  Let her know Hate.<br>
<br>
Slowly he traced his name over her loins in Elder Teir'dal, the most powerful tongue he knew.  He'd been taught by the necromancers that language and words are the most powerful tools, but he'd been taught by the whores that sex is the great equalizer.  He prayed to Innoruuk for strength as he wrote his name on her.<br>
<br>
As he finished the word &quot;Kaidan&quot; he felt a cool breeze slip across the back of his neck.  Suddenly he was very cold and very alone.  He looked around at the darkness and screamed, but his mouth made no sound.  Instead he could see himself flirting with her, playing still.  He forced his way back into control long enough to try and sing a battle chant that his friend Ratraz had taught him, but his Hate was lost in this battle.  It fell from his body faster than his clothes.<br>
<br>
He fought it.  He fought with all that he could, but he was not enough by himself.  He prayed for Shintou to come, to strike him down for his sins, but there was no balm for him.<br>
<br>
Innoruuk!  Father!<br>
<br>
He found himself struggling to unleash a Harm Touch, but even that was failed to him.<br>
<br>
Some time later the bite of sulfuric rain on his back snapped him out of the daze he was in.  The silly wood elf was dancing in the rain.  Let her die, he thought bitterly as he drug his clothes back on.<br>
<br>
&quot;Bah, are you Crazy!  It's hot!  There's sulfur in that rain!&quot;<br>
<br>
Shiden nearly fainted.  That was his voice!  He had called out to help her despite his wish for her dead!<br>
<br>
She giggled and came over to him as he picked up the shield and axe.  The smile on her face was bright and cheery.  The happiness melted off of Shiden's skin and he gripped the axe with all his might.<br>
<br>
With a snarl he lifted the axe, ready to bury it in her head.<br>
<br>
&quot;It echoes in that helmet!&quot; she cried happily and laughed.  Tears flooded to Shiden's eyes as he struggled to kill her, but try as he might he could not.  He was glad that the helmet hid his tears as he slung the axe over his back and forced out a weak laugh.<br>
<br>
&quot;Yes,&quot; he said, his voice weary.  He struggled to stand against the weakness in his knees.  &quot;I know.  Sometimes if I forget and shout I can't hear for hours afterwards.&quot;<br>
<br>
